PNO Fit and Magnon Dispersion

Generated on: 2025-03-27 17:00:30

Fitting Information

We use three types of function for the fit.

Gaussian function

for elastic and two phonons signal, defined as: $\sigma = \frac{\text{fwhm}}{2\sqrt{2 \ln(2)}}$ The FWHM is constrained to 39-39.5 meV (resolution limited).

Convoluted Damped harmonic oscillator

for magnon signal. We start from the original Dampled harmonic oscillator (DHO):

The prefactor ($\gamma^2\cdot\text{center}$) is to normalize the DHO function, so that the function takes the value of $\text{amplitude}$ at $x=\text{center}$, when the bose factor ignored. The bose factor is defined as:

The bose factor is cut off at 10 and -10 to avoid the divergence of the function. Note that the $x$ variable is in the unit of meV, thus the temperature of 15 K is approximately 1.3 meV, thus the demoniator 1.3 in the exponential function.

And the finally we convolve the DHO function with a Gaussian function. The Gaussian function has a FWHM of 39 meV.

Quadratic function

for background, defined as: Everything lower than zero is set to zero. The highest value is set to the amplitude. the peak locates at $x=\text{center}$. The prefactor $-\text{amplitude}/\text{center}^2$ is to ensure the function goes to zero at $x=0$. This way, everything below zero is set to zero.

Fitting Parameters

Analysis of magnon dispersion in un-doped Ni112 (PNO) along three directions in Q-space.

Parameter Value
elastic Gaussian function
Parameters: elastic_center, elastic_intensity, elastic_fwhm
Initial values: [0, 0.5, 39]
Bounds: [-20, 10], [0, 2], [38.5, 39.5]
phonon Gaussian function
Parameters: phonon_center, phonon_intensity, phonon_fwhm
Initial values: [30, 0.05, 39]
Bounds: [0, 60], [0, 0.2], [38.5, 39.5]
phonon2 Gaussian function
Parameters: phonon2_center, phonon2_intensity, phonon2_fwhm
Initial values: [80, 0.05, 39]
Bounds: [50, 110], [0, 0.2], [38.5, 39.5]
magnon Convoluted Damped harmonic oscillator
Parameters: magnon_center, magnon_intensity, magnon_gamma
Initial values: [100, 0.2, 100]
Bounds: [0, 400], [0, 10], [0, 1000]
background quadratic function
Parameters: peak_center_3, peak_amplitude_3
Initial values: [1000, 0.02]
Bounds: [800, 20000], [0, 0.1]
